duties:
Invigilating: CRI205H1 Fall 2024 final Exam on Thursday, December 19, 2024 (9:00 AM - 12:00 PM). Invigilator must arrive at least 30 minutes prior to the scheduled start time of the final exam.
Assistant Invigilators are responsible for a cursory check that every student has a valid ID before they are permitted into the exam hall.  Assistant Invigilators will distribute and collect examination materials and ensure all exam are accounted for and placed in alphabetical order;
Make announcements and report students problems;
Ensure that students comply with regulation with respect to exams;
Ensure that all mobiles and electronic devices are placed away from students;
Accompany students to the washrooms;
Observe each candidate in the examination room at all times;
Assisting the instructor and Chief Presiding Officer (CPO) with room management

•	marking student assignments, tests, and/or exams; 
•	responding to student enquiries; 
•	holding office hours to meet with students, if applicable;
•	occasional meetings with supervisor; 
•	facilitating guest lecture(s), tutorial(s), or other in-class projects, if applicable
